# motspilot — Cursor Integration Rules (MOTSTECH)

## Pipeline Awareness
- Check `.motspilot/workspace/tasks/` for pipeline state
- Requirements: `01_requirements.md`
- Architecture: `02_architecture.md`
- Read these BEFORE making changes

## Framework-Specific Rules
- Check `.motspilot/config` for the FRAMEWORK setting
- Read `prompts/frameworks/<FRAMEWORK>.md` for framework-specific conventions
- Follow the framework guide's API patterns, naming conventions, and coding standards

## Existing Codebase Rules
- NEVER modify existing method signatures
- NEVER restructure existing files as part of a feature
- ADD to existing files — don't rewrite them
- ADD routes — don't rename or remove existing ones
- Match existing code style (tabs vs spaces, comment style)
- Use the SAME auth mechanism the project already uses

## Migration Rules
- One logical action per migration file
- Never combine table creation + data seeding in one migration
- Migrations must be idempotent — guard with existence checks

## Screenshot Workflow
When the user pastes screenshots:
1. Analyze the UI shown
2. Write requirements matching the `01_requirements.md` template
3. Note existing UI patterns visible and match them
